<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77ad3ef1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s459e–5"><num value="459e–5">§ 459e–5.</num><heading> Acceptance of donations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may accept and use for purposes of sections 459e to 459e–9 of this title any real or personal property or moneys that may be donated for such purposes.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id77ad3ef2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/88/587/s6">Pub. L. 88–587, § 6</ref>, <date date="1964-09-11">Sept. 11, 1964</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/78/931">78 Stat. 931</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
